7":"1305–1387","1350–1426":"1350–1426","1370–1444":"1370–1444","1223–1303":"1223–1303","1225–Female":"1225–Deceased","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","abt 1350":"about 1350","1350":"1350","Abt 1345":"about 1345","1370":"1370","1270":"1270","1426":"1426","1305":"1305","1326":"1326","1303":"1303","1368":"1368","1225":"1225","1444":"1444","1345":"1345","1223":"1223","1300":"1300","1387":"1387","about 1365":"about 1365","County Tyrone, Irland":"County Tyrone, Ireland","Clannaboy, co. antrim, Ireland":"County Antrim, Ireland","Ireland":"Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Aine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional name, originally meaning ‘brightness’ or ‘radiance’; the name of the queen of the fairies in Celtic mythology, also used as an Irish equivalent of <i>Anne</i>, to which it is unrelated."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Aine Cumach O'Cathain of the Isles, Limavady was born about 1345, her father, King Guy O'Cathain - King of Keenaght, was 123 and her mother, Aonghas O'Cathan of Islay, was 121. She married Muircheartach Ceannfhada MacÉnri, Lord of Clandeboye Ó'Néill about 1365, in County Tyrone, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1368, in Ireland, at the age of 24."},"et":{"Abt 1345–1368":"umbes 1345–1368","1270–1326":"1270–1326","1345–1368":"1345–1368","1340–1395":"1340–1395","–1330":"–1330","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1305–1387":"1305–1387","1350–1426":"1350–1426","1370–1444":"1370–1444","1223–1303":"1223–1303","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","abt 1350":"umbes 1350","1350":"1350","Abt 1345":"umbes 1345","1370":"1370","1270":"1270","1426":"1426","1305":"1305","1326":"1326","1303":"1303","1368":"1368","1225":"1225","1444":"1444","1345":"1345","1223":"1223","1300":"1300","1387":"1387","about 1365":"umbes 1365","County Tyrone, Irland":"County Tyrone, Iirimaa","Clannaboy, co. antrim, Ireland":"County Antrim, Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1345–1368":"noin 1345–1368","1270–1326":"1270–1326","1345–1368":"1345–1368","1340–1395":"1340–1395","–1330":"–1330","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1305–1387":"1305–1387","1350–1426":"1350–1426","1370–1444":"1370–1444","1223–1303":"1223–1303","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","abt 1350":"noin 1350","1350":"1350","Abt 1345":"noin 1345","1370":"1370","1270":"1270","1426":"1426","1305":"1305","1326":"1326","1303":"1303","1368":"1368","1225":"1225","1444":"1444","1345":"1345","1223":"1223","1300":"1300","1387":"1387","about 1365":"noin 1365","County Tyrone, Irland":"County Tyrone, Irlanti","Clannaboy, co. antrim, Ireland":"County Antrim, Irlanti","Ireland":"Irlanti"},"fr":{"Abt 1345–1368":"environ 1345–1368","1270–1326":"1270–1326","1345–1368":"1345–1368","1340–1395":"1340–1395","–1330":"–1330","1300–Female":"1300–Décédée","1305–1387":"1305–1387","1350–1426":"1350–1426","1370–1444":"1370–1444","1223–1303":"1223–1303","1225–Female":"1225–Décédée","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","abt 1350":"environ 1350","1350":"135